> This kinda feels like a bandaid (which is not a bad thing in itself), do we know why the label was being offset in the first place? Is it possible to fix the root cause?

I discussed this with  Ashish — the issue isn't actually with the label being offset. The real problem lies in how the edge is drawn using D3's curve Basis. Because of the smoothing, the curve doesn't pass directly through the control points, which makes the label appear misaligned.

@ashishjain0512

