discussion_comments.comment_body:
I think I've found the issue that was causing the screenshots of the E2E tests to fail.

The issue is that we were updating `marginy` for subgraphs to use their parent value, and that was causing the positioning to shift very slightly.

If we instead only copy over the `ranksep` (i.e. the [`rankSpacing`](https://mermaid.js.org/config/schema-docs/config-defs-flowchart-diagram-config.html#rankspacing)) and the `nodesep` (i.e. the [`nodeSpacing`](https://mermaid.js.org/config/schema-docs/config-defs-flowchart-diagram-config.html#nodespacing)), it seems to work fine.

In the real world, however, it should would slightly modify the subgraphs of anybody that has set `rankSpacing`/`nodeSpacing`, so IMO, this should be in a MINOR release, not a PATCH release.

```suggestion
        const { ranksep, nodesep } = graph.graph();
        node.graph.setGraph({
          ...node.graph.graph(),
          ranksep,
          nodesep,
        });
```
